Q. st = 'Print only the words that start with s in this sentence'

Soln :   for word in st.split():
            if word[0].lower() == 's':
              print(word)


Q. Use a List Comprehension to create a list of all numbers between 1 and 50 that are divisible by 3.
Soln : mylist = [x for x in range(0,51) if x%3 == 0]

Q. Go through the string below and if the length of a word is even print "even!"
Soln : 
  st = 'Print every word in this sentence that has an even number of letters'
    for word in st.split():
      if len(word)%2==0:
        print(word)

Q. create a list of the first letters of every word in the string below:
Soln : 
  
st = 'Create a list of the first letters of every word in this string'
mylist = [word for word in st.split()]
for word in st.split():
    mylist.append(word[0])
print(mylist)
